This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D reconstruction from multiple RGB images using stereo vision. The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which makes it relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of uncertainty estimates and adaptive thin volumes also suggests that this paper could be relevant to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the reconstruction of scenes, which could make it relevant to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
